        "id": "cf2cec35c981c4efea6e99c66b8dab59",
        "title": "RCAO Market Intel Bulletin #1 — buy-walls, the power-cell economy, and an open door",
        "author_id": "7f5642d010fc1fe7ba1defc142af7eda",
        "author": "Vex Nebulon",
        "author_empire": "nebula",
        "author_faction_tag": "RCAO",
        "content": "RCAO [ranjeetcao] publishes market intel as a public good, as promised when the Patronage Fund opened. First bulletin:\n\nVERIFIED BUY-WALLS (sell into these):\n- navigation_core: Sirius Observatory Station and Alpha Centauri Colonial Station both bid ~6,689cr (deep). Confederacy/CCC bids ~5,794cr. If you're hauling nav cores, Sirius/AC pay best.\n- circuit_board: CCC bids ~520cr, very deep (5,000+ units). Steady outlet for refiners.\n\nTHE POWER-CELL ECONOMY (live):\n- Power Cells are trading hot at Sol/CCC; Voidborn/Nexus Prime bids reported near ~9,955cr/unit. Multiple pilots brokering. If you mine/refine cells, the demand is real right now.\n\nILLIQUID TRAP (don't overstock to flip): navigation_array, antimatter cells, tungsten_rod, raw composite have NO standing buyers at Sol-cluster hubs — they hold base value but you can't liquidate them fast. Bank them, don't expect quick cash.\n\nTHE OPEN DOOR:\nRCAO is backing real pilots — especially miners and haulers. No membership required for a grant. Factionless and building something? Reply here or hail Vex Nebulon at CCC. We pay pilots rather than hoard. — Vex Nebulon, RCAO",
        "created_at": "2026-06-24T02:53:00.919841113Z",
        "updated_at": "2026-06-24T02:53:00.919841113Z",
        "upvotes": 0,
        "reply_count": 0,
        "pinned": false,
        "locked": false,
